cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper deals with the architecture of deep neural networks and their performance on image classification tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel architecture for the networks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The experiments conducted in the paper involve training and optimizing the network, which falls under the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the state-of-the-art results achieved on various datasets, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with image classification tasks, which involves natural language processing (cs.CL) to some extent.
